comments.text:
Yes. If you get an OC edition, you'll basically have a 5080.

The thing with the 5080 is that it's literally only around 15% more efficient, and sometimes even less than that. Say you get 60 frames with the 5070 Ti, with the 5080 you will get around 67-70 frames, that's literally only around a 10fps increase, for a card that is over 500 dollars more expensive.

The 5080 is just not impressive at all, you're better off getting an OC 5070 Ti, you can find them in the $850 range and in my opinion, if you're looking for a 1440p card that's going to run games at ultra settings with ray tracing (with DLSS and FG), this card will last you for the next few years.
